<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.218722>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Polycirrus breviuncinatus sp. nov. Holotype (MZUSP 1220). A, entire worm; B, anterior end, ventral view; C, anterior end, dorsal view; D, anterior end, left lateral view; E, notochaetae, segment 8; F, uncinus, segment 18. Numbers refer to segments; ll = lower lip; P * = basal part of the prostomium; P (dp) = distal part of the prostomium; ul = upper lip. Scale bars: A = 500 µm; B – D = 150 µm; E = 20 µm; F = 5 µm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/218722/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.218723>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Polycirrus breviuncinatus sp. nov. Paratype 2 (MZUSP 1245). A, detail of the anterior end, ventral view; B, detail of the anterior end, dorsal view; C – D, anterior notopodia; E, detail of the tips of notochaetae, anterior notopodium; F – G, uncini, posterior neuropodia. Numbers refer to segments; ll = lower lip; P * = basal part of the prostomium; P (dp) = distal part of the prostomium; ul = upper lip. Scale bars: A = 100 μm, B – C = 50 μm, D, F = 2 μm, E = 20 μm, G = 5 μm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/218723/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

